{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTMzOTYxNzUw", "number": 15505, "title": "Add listener model for TaskThresholdMemoryRevokingScheduler", "bodyText": "Test plan - deployed to cluster, travis, wrote tests\nPreviously, TaskThresholdMemoryRevokingScheduler had only a polling based model for when a task allocates too much memory. This introduces a listener-based model instead which ensures that we do not have to wait for the polling thread to be scheduled.  Instead, we immediately schedule revoking.\n== RELEASE NOTES ==\n\nGeneral Changes\n* Add listener-based revocation model for spilling strategy PER_TASK_MEMORY_THRESHOLD", "createdAt": "2020-12-07T21:33:34Z", "url": "https://github.com/prestodb/presto/pull/15505", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "ca9466572da066f29c894d6b2ee5600aeab2dffa"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2021-01-07T09:07:03Z", "author": {"login": "sachdevs"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 9, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdj8jp7AFqTU0NjU1NzQ0Mw==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdtWIjigBqjQxNzMwMzcwNjk=", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NTQ2NTU3NDQz", "url": "https://github.com/prestodb/presto/pull/15505#pullrequestreview-546557443", "createdAt": "2020-12-07T21:37:50Z", "commit": {"oid": "4ac08606824504faa963b3594b1fa6bdff677ee4"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0wN1QyMTozNzo1MFrOIA71lw==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0wN1QyMTozNzo1MFrOIA71lw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDUzNzg1MTI4Nw==", "bodyText": "Not too sure what we think of this way of alerting the TaskThresholdMemoryRevokingScheduler. Not ideal but this is the cleanest way I could think of - other alternatives are passing the listener around somehow instead of piggybacking